#### Change all columns

You can use the `everything()` function to affect all columns (or remaining columns).

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mtcars %>% 
  tibble::rownames_to_column("names") %>% 
  head(8) %>%
  gt() %>% 
  cols_width(
    vars(names) ~ px(150),
    everything() ~ px(60)
  ) %>% 
  opt_table_lines()
```

